 Hi Jo Ee
 
 Thank you for your email.
 
 I think my team has met up with Dell previously. At the moment, it is a very busy period for us as it is our exams processing. Thank you for understanding.
 
 Best regards
 Anna
 
 From: Jo Ee Yeoh <joeeyeoh@boomi.com> 
 Sent: Friday, February 28, 2020 2:45 PM
 To: Anna YAP-TOO (NP) <Anna_YAP-TOO@np.edu.sg>
 Subject: Boomi iPaas Connect Everything, Engage Everywhere
 
 
 
 Dear Anna,
 It's Jo Ee from Dell Boomi. I thought to reconnect with Ngee Ann Polytechnic as we work with similar clients like yourself to help connect data, devices, applications and people.
 Now that it's the early of year, it may be a good time to do a health check on your current integration systems in preparation for the new business initiatives to come.
 Dell Boomi works with 7,800 clients, of which more than 130+ are Fortune 500 companies, include companies like LinkedIn, Docusign, Norvartis . With Dell Boomi, we help our clients execute changes  faster, across CRMs, ERPs, HRsystems, different legacy and modern systems through a low code APIs and integration approach via our iPaaS solution.
 One of customers, Linkedin was looking to implement a scalable integration solution to support rapid growth while being flexible enough to support multiple use cases. As a result of partnering  with Dell Boomi, Linkedin was able to process 30% more orders per analyst and reduced time to provision new clients by 30%.
 Perhaps we can get on a call this week to better understand how we can potentially support you in Ngee Ann Polytechnic.
 
 
  
 
 Jo Ee
 Account Manager, SEA
 
 A Dell Technologies Business

 J_Yeoh@dell.com
 1 Changi Business Park Central 1, Singapore

Hello,

In reviewing some recent orders created off of the 'DSG.com EDI 850 to NS' map, I notices the values coming from CTP03 seem to be rounding. I believe the number formatting needs to be adjusted to account for a second digit in cents.



This is similar to what we saw in QVC.com 850 process under Case: 00251288 about a month back.
